cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.CY 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and specifically focuses on detecting claims in text. It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it uses a language model and fine-tuning techniques to improve performance. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as it involves identifying and extracting relevant information from text, and cs.CY (Computers and Society) as it deals with analyzing opinionated claims in social media.
